**PART 1 --- How to Use This Guide & Key Contacts**

This guide identifies the governing codes, current adopted editions,
scope, and official sources for every major building trade across
residential, commercial, and industrial project types. It is organized
by trade and project type to allow quick lookup in the field or office.

**How to Read Each Code Table**

-   Code / Standard --- The official name and abbreviation of the code

-   Edition --- The specific year/edition currently adopted in Utah (may
    differ from the latest published edition)

-   Scope --- What work and building types the code governs

-   Official Source --- Where to obtain the actual code document for
    detailed requirements

  -----------------------------------------------------------------------
  **⚠ UTAH ADOPTION NOTE:** Utah uses a LEGISLATIVE adoption process ---
  meaning the state legislature must pass a bill to adopt each new code
  edition. This means Utah may lag behind the latest published edition.
  Always verify the current edition in force at le.utah.gov or
  codes.utah.gov before starting a project.

  -----------------------------------------------------------------------

