**3.2 Commercial Occupancy Classification (IBC Chapter 3)**

The IBC classifies all buildings by occupancy type. The classification
determines fire protection, egress, and construction requirements. Key
occupancy groups:

  ------------- -------------------- -----------------------------------------
  **Group**     **Occupancy Type**   **Examples**

  **A-1/A-2**   Assembly             Theaters, nightclubs, restaurants (\>50
                                     occupants)

  **B**         Business             Offices, banks, outpatient clinics,
                                     universities

  **E**         Educational          K-12 schools, day care \>6 children

  **F-1/F-2**   Factory/Industrial   Moderate/low hazard manufacturing

  **H-1 to      High Hazard          Explosives, flammables, toxic materials
  H-5**                              storage

  **I-1 to      Institutional        Hospitals, nursing homes, jails,
  I-4**                              supervised residential

  **M**         Mercantile           Retail stores, markets, motor fuel
                                     dispensing

  **R-1 to      Residential          Hotels, apartments, boarding houses
  R-4**                              

  **S-1/S-2**   Storage              Warehouses, parking garages, moderate/low
                                     hazard storage

  **U**         Utility/Misc.        Sheds, fences, tanks, towers,
                                     agricultural buildings
  ------------- -------------------- -----------------------------------------

