  -----------------------------------------------------------------------
  **PART 15 --- CODE ADOPTION CYCLE & WHERE TO OBTAIN CODES**

  -----------------------------------------------------------------------

**15.1 How Code Adoption Works in Utah**

Utah uses a LEGISLATIVE adoption process governed by Utah Code Title 15A
--- State Construction and Fire Codes Act. Key points:

-   The Utah State Legislature must pass a bill to adopt each new code
    edition --- there is no automatic adoption

-   Utah may lag 1--2 full code cycles behind the latest published
    edition

-   Local jurisdictions (Salt Lake City) follow the state adoption but
    may have local amendments in their city code

-   Always confirm the currently-in-force edition with the Authority
    Having Jurisdiction (AHJ) before starting design

**15.2 Current Utah Adopted Editions (2025--2026)**

